Stocks Resume Retreat; FTSE 100 Index Drop Led by Kazakhmys as Banks Rise

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-23T14:13:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/stocks-resume-retreat-ftse-100-index-drop-led-by-kazakhmys-as-banks-rise.html
U.K. stocks resumed their retreat
as a selloff in mining companies offset a rally in banks.  The FTSE 100 Index lost 0.6 percent to 5,012.85 at 3:12
p.m. in  London  after briefly paring losses in afternoon trade.
The gauge yesterday dropped 4.7 percent.  Mining companies paced the retreat, led by Kazakhmys Plc
and Xstrata Plc which both fell more than 4 percent. Lloyds
Banking Group Plc and Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc limited
losses on the FTSE 100, climbing 3.3 percent and 2.9 percent
respectively.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  